Consignment factors
Certain consignment factors may have an impact on the final decision concerning the  
best mode of transport for each individual shipment. These factors normally relate to specific characteristics of the order or load that may influence the choice of transport mode. Often 
only a few of these factors will apply, but sometimes several need to be taken into account  
for any given order or load. The main factors include those that are noted below:
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Routeing and through transit: there may be some distinct routing factors that must be adhered to and these may limit the options available to the shipper. Questions that 
might need to be considered include:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Is a direct route stipulated by the customer?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Are there countries through which the shipment may not travel?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Who is responsible for the through transit?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Who is paying for the freight costs?
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Distance: the distance that the load has to travel for delivery will have an influence on the mode of transport that might be considered:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ What is the distance to be moved?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Does distance restrict the options that are available?
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Type of cargo: cargo characteristics will certainly need to be carefully considered when 
the route and type of mode are determined:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ If it is bulk or general cargo, will limited alternatives mean that a certain specific route is preferable?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ If it is bulk or general cargo, are certain routes cheaper?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Does the cargo have specific characteristics (ie it may be perishable or high value) that make certain routes more attractive?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Is the cargo hazardous, if so are some routes unavailable?380 freight transport
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Quantity: the load quantity may influence the type of mode that can be used:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ full load: container and trailer options should be attractive;
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ part load: possibility of consolidation Ã¢â‚¬â€œ but time delays/as general cargo, but 
packaging implications;
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ small size: parcel, air freight, groupage/consolidation.
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Unit load: Is the load unitized, if not, is this an option and would it be cost effective?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Will unitization help?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Is it a small or large unit load?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Is containerization feasible?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Is groupage/consolidation an alternative?
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Priority: it is vital to be able to understand and balance the need for the urgency of an order against the cost of delivery:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ How soon must the goods reach their destination? This will influence the choice 
of mode.
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Does Ã¢â‚¬ËœUrgent!Ã¢â‚¬â„¢ really mean Ã¢â‚¬ËœUrgent!Ã¢â‚¬â„¢?
