 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Commodity value: as previously noted in discussions concerning trade-offs, the value of a consignment can significantly influence the choice of mode:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ How significant is the transport cost element to the consignment as a whole?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ If it is import/export, how is the commodity rated Ã¢â‚¬â€œ this may impact freight rates?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Will a fast, expensive mode enable reduced inventory holding and associated  
cost savings?
 Ã¢â‚¬Â¢Regular shipments: where regular shipments are to be made on certain routes it should be possible to negotiate competitive freight costs:
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ How often will these shipments be made?
 Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Should a contract be negotiated or is Ã¢â‚¬Ëœspot hireÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ adequate?
