A rigid vehicle is a goods vehicle where the motor unit and the carrying unit are constructed 
as a single vehicle (see Figure 27.2).
The term Ã¢â‚¬Ëœheavy goods vehicleÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ (HGV) is still in common parlance. However, since 1 April 1991 
in the UK the term has been replaced by Ã¢â‚¬Ëœlarge goods vehicleÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ (LGV) for legal purposes when 
